Nandi Bears Sports Club has been picked to host this year’s Kenya Cup final between Kabras Sugar and KCBRFC. The contest is set for this Saturday with Kabras picked as the host club. The sugar millers will be hoping to stop KCB who have won the gong for four straight seasons on their tracks. The match which will kick off at 2pm will be officiated by Moses Ndung’u . This will be the fourth final pitting the two clubs with KCB having emerged victorious in three occasions Kabras finished the regular season unbeaten while KCB RFC finished second losing only once 30-23 against Kabras at the same venue The western based Kabras side alongside KCB both won their semi finals encounters over the weekend outclassing Strathmore Leos and Menengai Oilers 39-19 and 35-17 respectively. Also Read: In last year’s final, the Ruaraka- based KCB defeated Kabras 23-15 to lift the title making for a tense weekend finale. Video Of The Day: | CHASING HOPE | KEMRI undertaking stem cell research for treatment of Leishmaniasis